[Student "S"]
{NORTH's 3\S bid, a double-jump, is a Splinter bid. It shows game-forcing strength, at 
least four cards in partner's suit, and a singleton or void in the Splintered suit.

SOUTH has just 14 points and the \S shortness in NORTH's hand doesn't improve her hand since 
she had just one \S loser anyway. She signs off in 4\H.}

